.TH TIMESIGNAL.CONF 5 "18 September 2025" "timesignal __VERSION__"
.
.
.SH NAME
.
.P
timesignal.conf \- configuration file for
.BR timesignal (1)
.
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.
.P
.nf
.I /etc/timesignal.conf
.fi
.
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.
.P
.BR timesignal (1)
can obtain its options from a configuration file.
.
.P
By default, it looks
for this file at
.IR /etc/timesignal.conf ,
although this can be changed using the
.RB ( \-c / \-\-config )
command\-line argument.
.
.P
The format of the configuration file consists of a series of
\fBOption\fR=\fIValue\fR assignments, one per line. This is similar to
the format used in INI files, but even simpler in that
.RB [ section ]
headers are not supported.
.
.P
The example below demonstrates all the essential features of the format:
.
.EX
.IP
# Everything on a line after \(lq#\(rq is a comment.
# Comments and blank lines are ignored.
.
.IP
# Option assignments have an option name,
# \(lq=\(rq as a separator, and an option value.
\fBOption\fR=\fIValue\fR
.
.IP
# Values may be quoted in regular (non\-curly) single or double quotes.
# They may also contain spaces, even if not quoted.
\fBOption\fR=\fI\(dqValue with spaces\(dq\fR
\fBOption\fR=\fI\(aqValue with spaces\(aq\fR
\fBOption\fR=\fIValue with spaces\fR
.
.IP
# A few options do not require specifying an option value.
# For such options, the value \fIOn\fR is implied.
\fBOption\fR
\fBOption\fR=\fIOn\fR
.
.IP
# Finally, option names and most option values
# (except for filenames) are not case\-sensitive.
\fBOption\fR=\fIValue\fR
\fBOPTION\fR=\fIVALUE\fR
\fBoption\fR=\fIvalue\fR
.EE
.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.
.P
Below are the options recognized in a configuration file, along with
brief descriptions, allowed values, and defaults. Options require values
unless otherwise specified. Some options default to special values that
cannot be explicitly set in a configuration file.
.
.P
Each configuration file option corresponds exactly to a command\-line
option. See
.BR timesignal (1)
for more details than may be shown here.
.
.SS Time station selection
.
.TP
.B station
Time station to emulate.
.br
May be
.IR BPC ,
.IR DCF77 ,
.IR JJY ,
.IR JJY60 ,
.IR MSF ,
or
.IR WWVB .
.br
Default is
.IR WWVB .
.
.SS Time signal options
.
.TP
.B base
Time base.
.br
Date and time in
.IR "YYYY\-MM\-DD HH:mm:ss" [ (+\-)hhmm ]
format, from
.I 1970\-01\-01 00:00:00+0000
to
.IR "9999\-12\-31 23:59:59+2359" .
.br
Default is the current system time (special value).
.
.TP
.B offset
User offset.
.br
Time quantity in
.RI [ +\- ] HH:mm:ss [ .SSS ]
format, from
.I \-23:59:59.999
to
.IR +23:59:59.999 .
.br
Default is
.IR 00:00:00.000 .
.
.TP
.B dut1
DUT1 value (only for MSF and WWVB).
.br
Number of milliseconds in
.RI [ +\- ] SSS
format, from
.I \-999
to
.IR +999 .
.br
Default is
.IR 0 .
.
.SS Timeout options
.
.TP
.B timeout
Time to run before exiting.
.br
Time quantity in
.I HH:mm:ss
format, from
.I 00:00:01
to
.IR 23:59:59 .
.br
Default is forever (special value).
.
.
.SS Sound options (rarely needed)
.
.TP
.B method
Output method.
.br
May be
.IR PipeWire ,
.IR PulseAudio ,
or
.IR ALSA .
.br
Default is autodetect (special value).
.
.TP
.B device
Output device (only for ALSA).
.br
ALSA device name.
.br
Default is
.IR default .
.
.TP
.B format
Output sample format.
.br
May be
.IR S16 ,
.IR S16_LE ,
.IR S16_BE ,
.IR S24 ,
.IR S24_LE ,
.IR S24_BE ,
.IR S32 ,
.IR S32_LE ,
.IR S32_BE ,
.IR U16 ,
.IR U16_LE ,
.IR U16_BE ,
.IR U24 ,
.IR U24_LE ,
.IR U24_BE ,
.IR U32 ,
.IR U32_LE ,
.IR U32_BE ,
.IR FLOAT ,
.IR FLOAT_LE ,
.IR FLOAT_BE ,
.IR FLOAT64 ,
.IR FLOAT64_LE ,
or
.IR FLOAT64_BE .
.br
Default is
.IR S16 .
.
.TP
.B rate
Output sample rate.
.br
May be
.IR 44100 ,
.IR 48000 ,
.IR 88200 ,
.IR 96000 ,
.IR 176400 ,
.IR 192000 ,
.IR 352800 ,
or
.IR 384000 .
.br
Default is
.IR 48000 .
.
.TP
.B channels
Output channels.
.br
Number of channels, from
.I 1
to
.IR 1023 .
.br
Default is
.IR 1 .
.
.TP
.B smooth
Smooth rapid gain changes in output waveform.
.br
Does not require a value.
.br
May be
.IR On ,
.IR Off ,
or not provided (same effect as
.IR On ).
.br
Default is
.IR Off .
.
.TP
.B ultrasound
Enable ultrasound output
.RB ( "MAY DAMAGE EQUIPMENT" ).
.br
Does not require a value.
.br
May be
.IR On ,
.IR Off ,
or not provided (same effect as
.IR On ).
.br
Default is
.IR Off .
.
.TP
.B audible
Make output waveform audible (for entertainment only).
.br
Does not require a value.
.br
May be
.IR On ,
.IR Off ,
or not provided (same effect as
.IR On ).
.br
Default is
.IR Off .
.
.SS Logging options
.
.TP
.B log
Log messages to a file.
.br
Path to a file.
.br
Default is none (special value).
.
.TP
.B syslog
Log messages to syslog.
.br
Does not require a value.
.br
May be
.IR On ,
.IR Off ,
or not provided (same effect as
.IR On ).
.br
Default is
.IR Off .
.
.TP
.B verbose
Increase logging verbosity.
.br
Does not require a value.
.br
May be
.IR On ,
.IR Off ,
or not provided (same effect as
.IR On ).
.br
Default is
.IR Off .
.
.TP
.B quiet
Suppress logging to console (and only console).
.br
Does not require a value.
.br
May be
.IR On ,
.IR Off ,
or not provided (same effect as
.IR On ).
.br
Default is
.IR Off .
.
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.
.P
